      "rationale": "Three mesh densities evaluated (coarse 1.0 mm, medium 0.6 mm, fine 0.4 mm global element size with local refinement at screw-rod interface). QoI change between medium and fine meshes: stiffness 0.9%, yield force 1.1%, force at 40 mm 0.8%. GCI < 0.6% for all QoIs. Fine mesh adopted for all production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Newton-Raphson convergence residuals < 1e-4 for all load steps; no unconverged increments in production runs.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear static analyses used Newton-Raphson iteration with force convergence criterion 1e-4. All 11 production simulations converged without bisection beyond the first load step. Solver log files archived."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation plan reviewed by independent analyst; input deck peer-reviewed prior to production runs.",
      "rationale": "A written simulation execution plan was prepared and independently reviewed by a second analyst before production runs. Boundary condition assignments, material property inputs, and contact definitions were checked against the validated template model. No use errors identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
