      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum FEA with bilinear isotropic hardening justified by published literature; contact modeled with augmented Lagrangian formulation.",
      "rationale": "Continuum mechanics representation of titanium alloy screw and rod is well established in the literature for quasi-static loading. Bilinear isotropic hardening parameters calibrated from published Ti-6Al-4V ELI coupon data. Augmented Lagrangian contact captures load transfer at screw-rod interface. Model form uncertainty quantified via sensitivity analysis."
    },
